{
  "stem": "13469.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But those listed all this correspondence that my father had with the Red Cross and with the Swiss embassy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because at that time, there was no British embassy in Holland anymore, because they were at war, Holland being under Germany was at war with Britain.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So there was no British embassy in Holland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all communications with British embassy was done via the Swiss embassy in Holland, in Hague.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they had to go to the Swiss embassy in Switzerland, and from there, to the British embassy in Switzerland, and from the British embassy in Switzerland to Britain, when there was any questions kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there we got certification that Eve was truly British.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we got a letter, apparently, from them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We haven't got the letter, but we did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Germans accepted that, that she was British, because, as I said, later on-- later on, I found that there was a difference between having-- we didn't have a British passport.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Eve didn't have a passport.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, why would a baby or a six-month-old in Britain, why would she have applied for a passport?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Maybe she should have done, but she didn't.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So she didn't have a British passport, but we did have a birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And now, my father, in 1942, got this confirmation by the British embassy in Switzerland, and the Red Cross, and the Swiss embassy, et cetera, that she was a British subject.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that entitled her to numerous exemptions.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, she didn't have to wear a star.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Children under six didn't have to wear a star anyway.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But Eve was just about on the border of six and seven in those days.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She didn't have to wear the star.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was not subject to various other rules.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
